Classes in edu.cmu.cs.stage3.alice.scenegraph used by edu.cmu.cs.stage3.alice.core.light
AmbientLight
          an ambient light illumates all visual elements equally.
useful in simulating bouncing light.
DirectionalLight
          a directional light emits parallel rays (as if it were at infinity).
the direction is inherent from absolute transformation of its container.
useful in simulating sunlight.
PointLight
          a point light emits rays in all directions.
the position is inherent from absolute transformation of its container.
useful in simulating a light bulb.
SpotLight
          a spot light emits a cone of light; behaving like a point light within its inner beam angle; and falling off exponentially between its inner and outer beam angles.
useful in simulating a luxo lamp.
